review_blob: decent everyday ale. standard brown ale. pours well, quickly settles and has a small thinn head. not a full bodied ale at all. finishes dry and doesnt linger. has a nutty aroma and is easy to drink.

this has been one of the best IPA ales I have ever tasted. The first thing you notice is the nice color and beautiful head that settles at the top. The aroma hit me with a hint of banana followed by a slight bit of clove. The taste was amazing, and with the alc % being nthat high, I was surprised to find so incredibly smooth. This one is a little more complex and I really had to think about all the complexity over the amazing taste. The taste is so smooth, I forgot about the strength. It goes down very nicely and finishes with a crisp palate that left me wanting another one.
beer_name: Avery The Maharaja Imperial India Pale Ale

review_blob: Not a bad brew. A little on the weak side for a wheat beer. Still, a very drinkable beer. Slight hints of banana, a little citrus.
pours out rather wimpy. At first I get the malty effect and then quickly fades into nothing. A very weak brew. Not one for those in search of the full bodied drink. Not a lot flavor here.
pours nicely leaving a good creamy ,thick head. Has nice hints of banana and is very fresh. Goes good with just about anything. Very good baseline Hefeweizen beer.

This ale is pretty good. It comes out smooth and is not overbearing in any way. It still has a strong aroma of hops out of the bottle but is easy to drink. A very good everyday ale. Medium bodied and has a fairly dry finish.

A vey strong ale. This ale is more like a meal. It very aromatic in the hops sense. It quite a bit  more bitter than expected, but still a decent brew. fairly pricey at around 12 bux a bottle. definite alcohol presence here. every drink leaves you staring at the glass again, wow!

This is by far my favorite everyday drink. This ale pours nicely and immediately gets your attention. The aroma is strong and sends your nose on a search for all the complexity in the mix. It is one of the best IPAs out there, period. A full bodied ale that commands a little respect. It is  a bit pricey, ranging from around 9 to 12 bux for the 4 pack. I think its worth it, it finishes leaving you wanting another one.

be careful. this one will come right out of the glass if youre hasty about it. has a wonderful flavor. rich creamy, and full of banana. This is a very nice unfiltered  wheat beer. This beer is awesome in the summer outside with a nice cigar.
rich malty, hints of coffee and chocolate.  nice frothy head. has a sweet taste and nice finish. This one works well with red meat. I had a few with a nice ribeye. My wife even liked this one
